cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

This paper proposes a method for unsupervised learning to train projection networks for generative adversarial networks (GANs). The paper specifically applies this method to a trained StyleGAN for image super-resolution and clustering. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, since the paper involves training a GAN, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also a likely sub-category. Finally, since the paper involves image processing and manipulation, cs.MM (Multimedia) is a possible sub-category as well.
